= Schleicher Enacts Concessions to Labor!

Presumably aiming to win over the unions' affiliated parties—the <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span> and the <span style="color: #c00000;">SPD</span>—and to bolster public confidence in his leadership at the grassroots level, Schleicher has enacted a new decree.

An eight-hour workday is now mandated across most industries, intended to "spread out" employment among more workers. The means test for unemployment insurance has been abolished, and welfare funding has been increased to offset years of austerity.

The <span style="color: #c00000;">Social</span> General has lived up to his nickname. Yet, cynically, the cost is clear—Schleicher now wields significant leverage over the unions, and many workers are beginning to shift their loyalty toward the chancellor, who delivers results, rather than the opposition parties. His image as a strongman, standing above the old parties, is slowly conditioning the workers to accept a more authoritarian system.

