With Schleicher granting concessions to the workers on his own initiative—rather than under pressure from the <span style="color: #c00000;">SPD</span>—he alone reaps the political rewards. Even some radicalized <span style="color: #700000;">Communist</span> workers begin to drift away, as the less ideological and politically disengaged prioritize their livelihoods over loyalty to their traditional parties.

But hey, at least the workers aren’t suffering as much anymore. This alone has led the ADGB to adopt a friendlier stance toward the chancellor, giving Schleicher growing influence within our party, using the unions as his middleman.